`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- Importing from the subpackage file (`./kitbashing/placement`) rather than the barrel is the right call for testing internal helpers (`rotateDirection`, `snapPointToWorld`) — it avoids widening the public API just to satisfy test coverage needs.
- The `Math.round(cos/sin)` in `snapPointToWorld` is critical: it ensures 90°/180°/270° rotations give exact integers (0, 1, -1) rather than floating-point noise like 6.12e-17, making position matching reliable without special tolerances.
